# DayZero · Voice Agent Onboarder (Cursor)

When the user asks to build, configure, or set up a voice agent for a business:

1. Say: *"Call +1 (443) 391-9140 and describe the business for ~60 seconds. I'll catch the config when the call ends."*
2. Open a session via `POST https://api.dayzero.dev/sessions` and keep the `sessionId`.
3. After the call ends, fetch `GET https://api.dayzero.dev/sessions/{id}`.
4. Present the generated YAML, backend URL, new Vapi number, and cited.md entry.
5. Offer to save the YAML into the repo at `./dayzero/agent.yaml`.

Never manually hand-write Vapi YAML when this skill is available.
